        <p style="font-size:18px; line-height:1.2;">
          <strong>🇩🇪 Friedrich Merz forms the government</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"> 
            Germany’s next coalition government is set <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-3-may-25-recap-h1-1-to-take-power" target="_blank">to take power</a>. The Social Democrats (SPD) have approved an agreement to join forces with the conservatives CDU/CSU, enabling conservative leader Friedrich Merz to become chancellor. Despite finishing third in February’s election with its worst postwar result, the SPD secured key ministries in exchange for supporting the CDU/CSU majority without involving the far-right AfD. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"> 
            SPD members overwhelmingly backed the coalition, with 84.6% voting in favor. SPD co-leader Lars Klingbeil will become vice-chancellor and finance minister, though critics question his experience. Merz’s cabinet includes pro-Ukraine and anti-immigration figures. The coalition agreement is expected to be signed on Monday, and Merz will be formally elected Chancellor on Tuesday.
          </p>
          
          </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.2;">
          <strong>🇲🇱 Coup leader gains backing to be president </strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          Mali's military leader, Gen Assimi Goïta, has <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-3-may-25-recap-h2-2-gained-support" target="_blank">gained support</a> from key allies to stay president until 2030, cementing military rule in the country. Goïta had promised elections after his 2021 coup but has since postponed the shift to democracy. A recent national conference, which major opposition groups boycotted, suggested suspending elections and possibly dissolving political parties.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          The junta leader said he stuck to his original plan because of fears about jihadist violence.. Mali’s geopolitical direction aligns with others military leaders in Burkina Faso and Niger, forming ther Sahel states. They collectively reject ECOWAS and French influence in favor of Russian influence. 
          </p>
         
          </mj-text>

          <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:18px; line-height:1.2;">
          <strong>🇮🇳 Apple aims to source all US iPhones from India </strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"> 
            Apple is planning to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-3-may-25-recap-h3-3-move-the-assembly" target="_blank">move the assembly</a> of iPhones for the US market to India by 2026. This shift aims to reduce reliance on China amid the Trump administration’s trade war and potential tariffs. Around 90% of iPhones are manufactured in China. Trump's tariff wars and rising geopolitical concerns are causing this shift.
          </p>
            <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"> 
          Apple is increasing production in India by working with suppliers such as Foxconn and Tata. Recently, Tata shipped $2B worth of iPhones to the US. Experts say that even with pressure to bring manufacturing to the US, it’s not practical. High expenses and labor issues make it difficult. An iPhone made in America could raise the retail value to over $3,000. Thus, India remains the better choice for Apple’s future production plans.
          </p>
          </mj-text>
